article.headline: UTEP 79, New Mexico State 61
article.story: EL PASO, Texas (AP) -- Jason Williams scored 15 of his 21 points in the first half as Texas-El Paso defeated New Mexico State 79-61 Saturday night. UTEP (7-2) won its third straight game despite shooting just 37 percent from the floor. New Mexico St. (3-6) lost its third straight game. Trevor Lawrence led the Aggies with 17 points and 10 rebounds. The Miners led 33-17 at halftime and held their lead by hitting 27-of-28 free throws in the second half. Omar Thomas and Filberto Rivera each scored 15 points for UTEP. The tandem combined for two field goals but connected on 25-of-26 free throws. Mike Mitchell added 12 points and Antwan Alexander had 10 for New Mexico St.. The Aggies hit 7-of-28 field goals in the first half as they dropped their second straight game this week to the Miners. UTEP beat New Mexico St. 75-64 Wednesday night.
